cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.BIO, cs.EM, cs.IT 

The paper discusses the physical design of a molecular communication receiver based on nanoscale biosensors, which involves aspects of nanoelectronics (cs.ET), biosensors (cs.BIO), electromagnetic theory (cs.EM), and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper explores the feasibility of designing a receiver with limited computational capacities, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
